-- PRESS DIGEST - Bulgaria - Oct 2
-- 
-- Thu Oct 02, 2014 02:03AM EDT
-- None



SOFIA, Oct 2 (Reuters) - These are some of the main stories in Bulgarian newspapers on Thursday. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

-- At least 10 people are missing after blasts at an explosives plant in northwestern Bulgaria. (24 Chasa, Standart, Monitor) -- The government approved a budget revision proposing to increase budget deficit to 4 percent of gross domestic product and raise 4.5 billion levs in new debt. The plan would have to be approved by the next parliament. (24 Chasa, Monitor, Capital Daily)